titlePage.byline:
BY JOHN OXENFORD AUTHOR OF Five Pounds
     Reward; Only a Half-penny; Reigning Favourite;
     Dice of Death, &c. &c.

sp.p:
Thank’ye, sir, thank’ye, sir, for throwing my basket out of window. That faithless
      monster’s present; I wish he had been here, I’d have asked Mr. Facile to throw him after it;
      I’m sure he’d have done it, he is so good-natured.

Oh, a very fine trick. Ah, no, you are in fun;

there was a note tied; I have it in my pocket. (pulls it out.)
      There, sir; pardon me blushing if it says anything soft.
